race.comment: BENGAL (14) ran his best race since joining the Luke Pepper yard when a close fifth in a 1200m Randwick Highway last start. Cherry ripe after three runs back and drops significantly in the weights. Expecting another bright performance and the early price on offer is very attractive. STRADA VARENNA (12) caught the eye in a BM78 over 1200m at Rosehill last start. The wide barrier becomes less of a problem after all the scratchings. Major player dropping back to midweek company with McDonald to steer. LADY OLENNA (10) returned to the winner's list with a tidy win over 1200m here three weeks ago. Talented mare who looks well in after the claim and can get the job done again. SHALAA GOLD (3) was a shade disappointing first up at Warwick Farm but probably found the 1000m too sharp. Record at this trip is hard to fault and has placed 3/3 second-up so his credentials are strong. ACTION KING (5) demands attention after bolting in at Wagga last start.
